name: MEDIUM-VOLTAGE SUB-TRANSMISSION EXPANSION SECTOR PROJECT
info: The proposed project will expand the supply of reliable and cost effective grid-electricity in Kampong Thom, Kampong Cham, Siem Reap, Kandal and Banteay Meanchey province in Cambodia. It will (i) expand the electricity transmission infrastructure by constructing 2,110 kilometer (km) of 22 kilovolt (kV) sub-transmission lines , (ii) support the implementation of the project, and (iii) improve the operational effectiveness and efficiency of Electricite du Cambodge.
